# UI Design System Rules

## 1. Design Tokens Management

### 1.1 Color System
- All colors must be defined in `:root` CSS variables in `globals.css`
- Use semantic naming convention: `--{category}-{shade}`
- Maintain coffee-inspired palette as primary theme
- All color references in components must use CSS variables, not hardcoded values

### 1.2 Typography
- Font families defined in CSS variables: `--font-{name}`
- Font sizes use CSS variables: `--text-{size}`
- Font weights use CSS variables: `--font-weight-{name}`
- Line heights use CSS variables: `--leading-{size}`

### 1.3 Spacing
- All margins/paddings use CSS variables: `--space-{size}`
- Follow 4px base unit system (4, 8, 12, 16, 20, 24, 32, 40, 48, 64px)
- Component-specific spacing: `--component-{name}-spacing`

### 1.4 Border Radius
- Global border radius variable: `--border-radius`
- Set to 0 for sharp edges (current requirement)
- Can be easily changed for future design updates
- Use utility classes for different radius sizes

## 2. Icon System

### 2.1 Icon Source Consistency
- Use only **react-icons** library for all icons
- No mixing icon libraries (react-icons, lucide-react, heroicons, etc.)
- Create icon wrapper components for consistent sizing and styling
- All icons must be semantic and accessible

### 2.2 Icon Usage Rules
- **NO EMOJIS IN TEXT** - strictly forbidden in UI text
- Use icons only for visual enhancement, not as primary content
- Icons must have proper aria-labels for screen readers
- Consistent sizing: use CSS variables for icon dimensions
- Icons should match the coffee theme color palette

