```

## 4. Layout System

### 4.1 Layout Principles
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Consistent spacing using design tokens
- Semantic HTML5 structure
- Logical content hierarchy
- Accessible navigation patterns

### 4.2 Grid System
- Use CSS Grid for complex layouts
- Define grid gaps using spacing variables
- Responsive breakpoints: sm(640px), md(768px), lg(1024px), xl(1280px)
- Grid templates for common layouts:
  - `--grid-2-cols`: 50/50 split
  - `--grid-3-cols`: 33/33/33 split
  - `--grid-sidebar`: main + sidebar

### 4.3 Stack System
- Use Flexbox for single-axis layouts
- Define stack spacing variables: `--stack-{size}`
- Direction variants: vertical, horizontal
- Alignment options: start, center, end, stretch
- Responsive stacking (horizontal on desktop, vertical on mobile)

### 4.4 Container System
- Max-width containers for content
- Consistent padding using spacing variables
- Center alignment by default
- Full-width option for hero sections

### 4.5 Layout Components
```
src/components/ui/layout/
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ Container.tsx       # Max-width container
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ Grid.tsx           # CSS Grid wrapper
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ Stack.tsx          # Flexbox stack
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ Section.tsx        # Content sections
в””в”Ђв”Ђ index.ts          # Exports
```

### 4.6 Responsive Design Rules
- Mobile-first approach always
- Test on actual devices, not just browser resize
- Touch-friendly tap targets (minimum 44px)
- Readable text sizes on all devices
- Consistent breakpoint usage

## 5. Component Architecture

### 5.1 Generic Component Requirements
- All UI components must be generic and reusable
- Use composition over inheritance
- Accept `className` prop for custom styling
- Use forwardRef for DOM elements when needed
- Support all standard HTML attributes

### 5.2 Required Base Components
- **Button**: Multiple variants (primary, secondary, ghost, outline)
- **Modal**: Configurable sizes, animations, accessibility
- **Input**: Text, email, password, number variants
- **Card**: Flexible container component
- **Badge**: Status indicators, labels
- **Avatar**: User images with fallbacks
- **Dropdown**: Menu, select, context menu
- **Toast**: Notifications system
- **Skeleton**: Loading states
- **Spinner**: Loading indicators (use `@/components/ui/Spinner` everywhere)

