## 6. Styling Rules

### 6.1 CSS-in-JS vs Utility Classes
- Use Tailwind utility classes for styling
- Use CSS variables for dynamic values
- Avoid inline styles except for dynamic calculations
- Use CSS modules only for complex animations

### 6.2 Responsive Design
- Mobile-first approach
- Use Tailwind responsive prefixes (sm:, md:, lg:, xl:)
- Define breakpoints in CSS variables
- Test on all screen sizes

### 6.3 Dark Mode Support
- Use `prefers-color-scheme: dark` media query
- Define color pairs for light/dark themes
- Test color contrast ratios

## 7. Accessibility Standards

### 7.1 ARIA Support
- All interactive elements need proper ARIA labels
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Implement keyboard navigation
- Screen reader compatibility

### 7.2 Focus Management
- Visible focus indicators
- Logical tab order
- Focus trapping in modals
- Skip links for navigation

### 7.3 Color Contrast
- WCAG AA compliance minimum
- Test contrast ratios
- Don't rely on color alone for information

## 8. Animation and Transitions

### 8.1 Motion Principles
- Subtle, purposeful animations
- Consistent timing functions
- Respect user preferences (prefers-reduced-motion)
- Performance optimized (transform, opacity)

### 8.2 Transition Standards
- Use CSS variables for durations: `--transition-{speed}`
- Standard easing functions: `--ease-{type}`
- Consistent hover states
- Loading state animations

## 9. State Management

### 9.1 Component States
- Default, hover, active, disabled, loading, error
- Consistent visual feedback
- Clear state transitions
- Error state handling

### 9.2 Form Validation
- Real-time validation feedback
- Clear error messages
- Success state indicators
- Accessible error announcements

## 10. Performance Guidelines

### 10.1 Rendering Optimization
- Use React.memo for expensive components
- Implement proper key props
- Avoid unnecessary re-renders
- Lazy load heavy components

### 10.2 CSS Optimization
- Minimize CSS custom properties usage
- Use efficient selectors
- Avoid layout thrashing
- Optimize images and assets

## 11. Testing Requirements

### 11.1 Unit Tests
- Test all component props
- Test user interactions
- Test accessibility features
- Test error states

### 11.2 Visual Testing
- Screenshot testing for UI consistency
- Cross-browser testing
- Responsive design testing
- Dark mode testing

## 12. Documentation Standards

### 12.1 Component Documentation
- JSDoc comments for all props
- Usage examples
- Accessibility notes
- Design tokens used

### 12.2 Storybook Integration
- Visual component library
- Interactive examples
- Design token documentation
- Accessibility testing

## 13. Migration Strategy

### 13.1 Gradual Migration
- Migrate one component at a time
- Maintain backward compatibility
- Test thoroughly before deployment
- Update documentation

### 13.2 Legacy Code Support
- Wrapper components for old code
- Gradual deprecation warnings
- Migration guides
- Support during transition period

